### ===========================================================================
### Ticket Endpoints — Test Data
### Base URL: http://localhost:3000
### Tool: VS Code REST Client  (Cmd/Ctrl+Alt+R to run a request)
###
### Execution order:
###   1. Sign Up (admin + 2 participants)
###   2. Sign In (admin + alice)
###   3. Create Hackathon (admin)
###   4. Alice joins hackathon
###   5. Alice creates a team
###   6. POST /teams/:id/tickets       — request help (participant)
###   7. GET  /hackathon/:id/tickets   — view open tickets (admin)
###   8. PUT  /tickets/:id/claim       — admin claims ticket
###   9. PUT  /tickets/:id/resolve     — resolve (admin or member)
###  10. Error-case tests
### ===========================================================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000

# -----------------------------------------------
# Paste IDs here after running each step
# -----------------------------------------------
@hackathonId = REPLACE_WITH_HACKATHON_ID
@teamId      = REPLACE_WITH_TEAM_ID
@ticketId    = REPLACE_WITH_TICKET_ID

# -----------------------------------------------
# Paste session tokens after signing in
# -----------------------------------------------
@adminSession = REPLACE_WITH_ADMIN_SESSION
@aliceSession = REPLACE_WITH_ALICE_SESSION
@bobSession   = REPLACE_WITH_BOB_SESSION


### ===========================================================================
### STEP 1a — Sign Up: Admin user
### ===========================================================================
# @name signUpAdmin
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/sign-up/email
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Hackathon Admin",
  "email": "admin@hackathon.dev",
  "password": "Admin1234!",
  "role": "ADMIN"
}

###

### ===========================================================================
### STEP 1b — Sign Up: Participant Alice
### ===========================================================================
# @name signUpAlice
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/sign-up/email
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Alice Participant",
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "Alice1234!"
}

###

### ===========================================================================
### STEP 1c — Sign Up: Participant Bob (outsider — for error test)
### ===========================================================================
# @name signUpBob
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/sign-up/email
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Bob Outsider",
  "email": "bob@example.com",
  "password": "Bob12345!"
}

###

### ===========================================================================
### STEP 2a — Sign In: Admin
### Copy token from response → @adminSession above
### ===========================================================================
# @name signInAdmin
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/sign-in/email
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@hackathon.dev",
  "password": "Admin1234!"
}

###

### ===========================================================================
### STEP 2b — Sign In: Alice
### Copy token from response → @aliceSession above
### ===========================================================================
# @name signInAlice
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/sign-in/email
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "Alice1234!"
}

###

### ===========================================================================
### STEP 2c — Sign In: Bob (only needed for error test)
### Copy token from response → @bobSession above
### ===========================================================================
# @name signInBob
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/sign-in/email
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "bob@example.com",
  "password": "Bob12345!"
}

###

### ===========================================================================
### STEP 3 — Create Hackathon  [Admin]
### Copy returned "id" → @hackathonId above
### ===========================================================================
POST {{baseUrl}}/hackathon
Content-Type: application/json
Cookie: better-auth.session_token={{adminSession}}

{
  "name": "Summer Hack 2026",
  "description": "A 48-hour hackathon for creative builders.",
  "startsAt": "2026-07-01T09:00:00.000Z",
  "endsAt": "2026-07-03T09:00:00.000Z"
}

###

### ===========================================================================
### STEP 4a — Alice joins the hackathon  [Alice]
### ===========================================================================
POST {{baseUrl}}/hackathon/{{hackathonId}}/join
Cookie: better-auth.session_token={{aliceSession}}

###

### ===========================================================================
### STEP 4b — Bob also joins (so error test is only about team membership)
### ===========================================================================
POST {{baseUrl}}/hackathon/{{hackathonId}}/join
Cookie: better-auth.session_token={{bobSession}}

###

### ===========================================================================
### STEP 5 — Alice creates a team  [Alice]
### Copy returned "id" → @teamId above
### ===========================================================================
POST {{baseUrl}}/hackathon/{{hackathonId}}/teams
Content-Type: application/json
Cookie: better-auth.session_token={{aliceSession}}

{
  "name": "Team Alpha"
}

###

### ===========================================================================
### ✅ HAPPY PATH 1 — POST /teams/:id/tickets
### Alice (team member & hackathon participant) requests help
### Copy returned "id" → @ticketId above
### Expected: 201 — "Help request submitted successfully"
### ===========================================================================
POST {{baseUrl}}/teams/{{teamId}}/tickets
Content-Type: application/json
Cookie: better-auth.session_token={{aliceSession}}

{
  "issue": "We are having trouble connecting to the PostgreSQL database. The connection string looks correct but we keep getting a timeout error after 30 seconds. We are using Prisma with a pooled connection string from Supabase."
}

###

### ===========================================================================
### ✅ HAPPY PATH 2 — GET /hackathon/:id/tickets
### Admin views all OPEN tickets for the hackathon
### Expected: 200 — list of open tickets, oldest first
### ===========================================================================
GET {{baseUrl}}/hackathon/{{hackathonId}}/tickets
Cookie: better-auth.session_token={{adminSession}}

###

### ===========================================================================
### ✅ HAPPY PATH 3 — PUT /tickets/:id/claim
### Admin claims the ticket (OPEN → CLAIMED, mentorId set to admin)
### Expected: 200 — "Ticket claimed successfully"
### ===========================================================================
PUT {{baseUrl}}/tickets/{{ticketId}}/claim
Cookie: better-auth.session_token={{adminSession}}

###

### ===========================================================================
### ✅ HAPPY PATH 4a — PUT /tickets/:id/resolve  (by Admin)
### Expected: 200 — "Ticket resolved successfully"
### ===========================================================================
PUT {{baseUrl}}/tickets/{{ticketId}}/resolve
Cookie: better-auth.session_token={{adminSession}}

###

### ===========================================================================
### ✅ HAPPY PATH 4b — Create a second ticket and let Alice (team member) resolve it
### 1. Create the ticket
### ===========================================================================
# @name createTicket2
POST {{baseUrl}}/teams/{{teamId}}/tickets
Content-Type: application/json
Cookie: better-auth.session_token={{aliceSession}}

{
  "issue": "Our React frontend fails to fetch from the backend API. CORS headers seem to be missing even though we configured them in NestJS. We need guidance on setting up a reverse proxy or proper CORS options."
}

###

### 2. Paste the new ticket ID and resolve it as Alice
PUT {{baseUrl}}/tickets/REPLACE_WITH_TICKET2_ID/resolve
Cookie: better-auth.session_token={{aliceSession}}

###


### ===========================================================================
### ❌ ERROR 1 — Non-team-member requests help
### Bob is a hackathon participant but not on Team Alpha
### Expected: 403 Forbidden — "Only team members can request help for this team"
### ===========================================================================
POST {{baseUrl}}/teams/{{teamId}}/tickets
Content-Type: application/json
Cookie: better-auth.session_token={{bobSession}}

{
  "issue": "I am a hackathon participant but not on this team. This ticket creation should be rejected with a 403 error."
}

###

### ===========================================================================
### ❌ ERROR 2 — Participant tries to view hackathon tickets (admin only)
### Expected: 403 Forbidden
### ===========================================================================
GET {{baseUrl}}/hackathon/{{hackathonId}}/tickets
Cookie: better-auth.session_token={{aliceSession}}

###

### ===========================================================================
### ❌ ERROR 3 — Participant tries to claim a ticket (admin only)
### Expected: 403 Forbidden
### ===========================================================================
PUT {{baseUrl}}/tickets/{{ticketId}}/claim
Cookie: better-auth.session_token={{aliceSession}}

###

### ===========================================================================
### ❌ ERROR 4 — Double claim: ticket already claimed
### Run HAPPY PATH 3 first, then run this
### Expected: 409 Conflict — "This ticket has already been claimed by another admin"
### ===========================================================================
PUT {{baseUrl}}/tickets/{{ticketId}}/claim
Cookie: better-auth.session_token={{adminSession}}

###

### ===========================================================================
### ❌ ERROR 5 — Double resolve: ticket already resolved
### Run HAPPY PATH 4a first, then run this
### Expected: 409 Conflict — "This ticket is already resolved"
### ===========================================================================
PUT {{baseUrl}}/tickets/{{ticketId}}/resolve
Cookie: better-auth.session_token={{adminSession}}

###

### ===========================================================================
### ❌ ERROR 6 — Validation: issue too short (< 10 characters)
### Expected: 400 Bad Request — minLength constraint
### ===========================================================================
POST {{baseUrl}}/teams/{{teamId}}/tickets
Content-Type: application/json
Cookie: better-auth.session_token={{aliceSession}}

{
  "issue": "short"
}

###

### ===========================================================================
### ❌ ERROR 7 — Ticket not found
### Expected: 404 Not Found — "Ticket not found"
### ===========================================================================
PUT {{baseUrl}}/tickets/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/claim
Cookie: better-auth.session_token={{adminSession}}

###
